      "options": {
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false
        },
        "content": "## TTFT = API Server Delay + Engine Queue Time + Prefill Compute\n\nvLLM sets `arrival_time` in the API server's Renderer (`base.py`), but `queue_time` starts from `queued_ts` when the engine core receives the request. The derived **API Server Delay** panel below computes `avg(TTFT) - avg(queue_time) - avg(prefill_time)` per pod, which equals `queued_ts - arrival_time` — the time the request spends in the API server process between the Renderer and engine forwarding.\n\nUnder high concurrency, a single API server process (`--api-server-count 1`) streaming tokens for hundreds of concurrent requests can become the bottleneck. Scale with `--api-server-count`.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.3.0",
      "transparent": true,
      "type": "text"
    },
